React Components :
---------------------
    Two types of react components

        1. Class components  - [oops concepts]
        2. Function components. [React Team preffered this FC component]
        

    1. Class components
    ------------------------

        Class components is based on oops technique instance of objects.


        import { Component } from "react";
        
          export class [Comp_name] extends Component {

                render(){

                    return (
                        <div>
                            <h1> Welcome to React Class components </h1>
                            <p>Hello React js </p>

                         </div>
                    )
                }
            }


        State Mangement
        ---------------

         class Comp_name extends React.Component {

                constructor(){
                    super()
                    this.state = { welcomeMsg = 'Welcome to react JS'}

                }

                rendr(){

                    return (
                        <div>
                            <h1> { this.state.welcomeMsg } </h1>
                            <p>Hello React js </p>

                         </div>
                    )
                }
            }







        1.1  Class component life cycle
        ----------------------------------


            constructor()           ->     first invoking the objects
            render()                ->     method is required, and is the method that actually outputs the HTML to the DOM.
            componentWillmount()    ->     after render tempalte invoking
            componentDidMount()     ->     method is called after the component is rendered.


     
    
        
        
        Example 2 
        ----------

           


        Example 3
        ----------
            class Comp_name extends React.Component {

                constructor(){
                    super()
                    this.state = { welcomeMsg = 'Welcome to react JS'}
                }

                componentDidMount(){

                    console.log("component Didmount called")
                    
                }
                componentWillMount(){

                    console.log("component will mount called")
                }

                rendr(){

                    return (
                        <div>
                            <h1> {this.state.welcomeMsg } </h1>
                            <p>Hello React js </p>

                         </div>
                    )
                }
            }



STATE and UPDATE STATE
------------------------


class FirstProgram extends React.Component {

  constructor(){
    super()
    this.state = {
       name : 'Saravanan',
       age : 27
    }
  }

  render(){
    return <div>
        <h1>Name : {this.state?.name}</h1> 
        <button onClick = {()=> this.setState({name:'Rajesh'}) } > update name </button>

        <p> age : {this.state?.age}</p> 
        <button onClick = {()=> this.setState({age : 30})}> update age </button>
        
    </div>
  }
}